{"session_id":"svc-1778085383841949830","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-06T16:36:26.000013813Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","resolved_harness":"codex","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"gpt-5.4-mini","work_dir":"/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-5d154c5d-20260506T163621-e616f678","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260506T163621-e616f678/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260506T163621-e616f678/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If you write `.ddx/executions/20260506T163621-e616f678/no_changes_rationale.txt`, it MUST carry one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;one-line shell command\u0026gt;` — the loop runs it (cwd = project root, 60s); exit 0 closes the bead, non-zero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: needs_investigation` + `reason: \u0026lt;why\u0026gt;` — bead stays open for triage.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Bare rationales (\u0026#34;nothing to do\u0026#34;) are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260506T163621-e616f678/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260506T163621-e616f678/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Bead overrides project defaults\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead description and AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and conservative project defaults (YAGNI, DOWITYTD, no-docs-unless-asked) in this worktree — write whatever the bead asks for.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-5d154c5d\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eagent: add DDx-scoped task execution cleanup manager\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;DDx-created temporary execution resources do not have one shared cleanup owner. Inline attempt cleanup, orphan recovery, and liveness cleanup are spread across attempt code and ad hoc test helpers, which let stale /tmp/ddx-exec-wt directories and registered orphan worktrees accumulate until /tmp ran out of inodes.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:257-279 defines the DDx temp worktree root and naming convention, but there is no cleanup manager that owns that root.\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:296-324 exposes WorktreeAdd/Remove/List/Prune primitives, but no production code uses them to reconcile stale registered vs unregistered DDx worktrees before attempts.\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/agent/run_state.go:16-29 records one live attempt path, but it does not model cleanup ownership, preserved state, stale PID/session liveness, or partial setup directories.\u0026#xA;- docs/helix/02-design/solution-designs/SD-025-task-execution-lifecycle.md:202-266 defines the cleanup manager roots, ownership metadata, entry points, and conservative deletion rules now missing in code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;- Add a focused cleanup manager under cli/internal/agent, e.g. execution_cleanup.go, with injectable filesystem/git/liveness probes for tests.\u0026#xA;- Teach it to inspect the configured DDx temp worktree root, project git worktree list, run-state/liveness files, and legacy .ddx/executions/.ddx/runs evidence roots.\u0026#xA;- Implement conservative deletion: remove only DDx-owned stale unregistered dirs, stale registered DDx worktrees, stale liveness files, and partial setup dirs; preserve published evidence, preserve refs, and active liveness.\u0026#xA;- Return a structured cleanup summary with removed path counts, bytes/inodes where measurable, warnings, and blocked errors.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Do not wire the manager into ddx try/work loops here; that is covered by sibling beads.\u0026#xA;- Do not add the operator CLI command here; that is covered by a sibling bead.\u0026#xA;- Do not implement .ddx/executions to .ddx/runs migration.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. TestExecutionCleanup_RemovesStaleUnregisteredDDxTempDirs creates DDx-owned stale dirs under a temp DDX_EXEC_WT_DIR and verifies the manager removes only stale DDx-owned dirs.\u0026#xA;2. TestExecutionCleanup_RemovesRegisteredStaleWorktree verifies a registered DDx worktree with stale/missing liveness is removed through GitOps.WorktreeRemove and git worktree prune.\u0026#xA;3. TestExecutionCleanup_PreservesActiveAndPreservedAttempts verifies live PID/session liveness, preserved worktree metadata, refs/ddx/iterations/*, complete .ddx/runs, and complete .ddx/executions bundles are not removed.\u0026#xA;4. TestExecutionCleanup_ReportsSummary verifies removed counts, warnings, and resource observations are returned in a structured summary usable by work events and CLI output.\u0026#xA;5. The cleanup manager is invoked by tests through public package functions/types, not unstructured shell cleanup snippets.\u0026#xA;6. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/agent/... -run \u0026#34;TestExecutionCleanup\u0026#34; -count=1 passes.\u0026#xA;7. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, area:agent, area:git, kind:implementation, reliability, spec:FEAT-010, spec:SD-025, cleanup\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-f3dfde0d\" spec-id=\"SD-025\" base-rev=\"0e753ea385f5695287c617e4a7e901904067f298\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260506T163621-e616f678\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cref id=\"SD-025\" path=\"docs/helix/02-design/solution-designs/SD-025-task-execution-lifecycle.md\"\u003eSolution Design: Task Execution Lifecycle\u003c/ref\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"attempt_id":"20260506T163621-e616f678","base_rev":"0e753ea385f5695287c617e4a7e901904067f298","bead_id":"ddx-5d154c5d","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260506T163621-e616f678","correlation_id":"ddx-5d154c5d:20260506T163621-e616f678","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260506T163621-e616f678/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"e33dbc833c8af963096